The preprocessing stage focused on converting raw UAE Labour Law PDF documents into clean machine-readable text files. Using Python and the PyPDF2 library, text was extracted page by page from each PDF document. Several cleaning operations were then applied, including removing page numbers, URLs, email addresses, and unnecessary whitespace. Regular expressions were used to identify formatting artifacts and normalize the text structure. One challenge encountered during preprocessing was inconsistent formatting across some pages, which occasionally produced spacing issues after extraction. The cleaned documents were saved as .txt files in the processed data directory, making them suitable for chunking, embedding generation, and retrieval tasks in later stages of the RAG pipeline.